    <item>
      <title>Introduction to Ecological Niche Modeling</title>
      <link>https://mauriciovancine.github.io/talk/talk-enm-gggc/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2020 10:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://mauriciovancine.github.io/talk/talk-enm-gggc/</guid>
      <description>
&lt;script src=&#34;https://mauriciovancine.github.io/talk/talk-enm-gggc/index_files/header-attrs/header-attrs.js&#34;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The Ecological Niche Models (ENM) relate species occurrence data with their environmental conditions to estimate the species niche and thus predict new areas of possible distribution. In this lecture, I talked about the main concepts, input data and applications of this approach in the area of Ecology and performed a practice in R.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
